      "content": "thanks. that's a good start. specifically, i want to tackle the counter-arguments that critics usually bring up, like how redistribution undermines meritocracy or hurts individual incentive. can you help me frame those opposing views in a way that shows they're fundamentally flawed or based on outdated ideas? i want to show why the meritocracy argument doesn't actually hold up when you look at systemic racism.",
